---
import DiscoveryPage from '../layouts/DiscoveryPage.astro';
---

<DiscoveryPage
  title="Relation Dynamics — Psyche"
  description="Understand how Psyche models relation moves, dyadic fields, open loops, and repair friction instead of treating emotions as labels."
  page="relation-dynamics"
  kicker="relation engine / dyadic field"
  titleCn="关系动力学，而不是情绪标签"
  titleEn="Relation dynamics, not emotion labels"
  leadCn="Psyche 最关键的升级，不是让 AI 更会说“我有感觉”，而是开始建模你刚刚对它做了什么、双方关系因此变成了什么，以及这种变化如何留下后果。"
  leadEn="Psyche's important leap is not better emotional prose. It is modeling what you just did to the agent, what the dyad became because of it, and how that change leaves consequences."
  stats={[
    { value: '6', labelCn: '关系动作', labelEn: 'relation moves', noteCn: 'bid / breach / repair / test / withdrawal / claim', noteEn: 'bid / breach / repair / test / withdrawal / claim' },
    { value: '4', labelCn: '关系残留', labelEn: 'carry terms', noteCn: 'open loops / silent carry / hysteresis / repair friction', noteEn: 'open loops / silent carry / hysteresis / repair friction' },
    { value: '1', labelCn: '统一关系场', labelEn: 'dyadic field', noteCn: 'distance / safety / pressure / unfinished tension', noteEn: 'distance / safety / pressure / unfinished tension' },
  ]}
  links={[
    { href: '/compare', labelCn: '和旧方案对比', labelEn: 'compare', noteCn: '为什么它不只是 persona 或记忆层', noteEn: 'why this is not just persona or memory' },
    { href: '/demo', labelCn: '看关系余震', labelEn: 'watch residue', noteCn: '看 breach → work → residue 继续存在', noteEn: 'watch breach → work → residue carry forward' },
    { href: '/work-vs-private', labelCn: '工作 / 私人面', labelEn: 'work vs private', noteCn: '关系余震如何穿过任务回合', noteEn: 'how relation residue survives task turns' },
  ]}
>
  <section class="discovery-section">
    <h2 class="section-label"><span class="cn">最小单位：关系动作</span><span class="en">Minimum unit: relation moves</span></h2>
    <p class="section-intro"><span class="cn">Psyche 不先问“现在是什么情绪”，而是先问“这句话在关系里是什么动作”。这是它和普通情感插件分叉的地方。</span><span class="en">Psyche does not start with “what emotion is this?” It starts with “what move did this utterance make in the relationship?” That is the fork from ordinary emotion plugins.</span></p>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="discovery-card"><h3>bid</h3><p><span class="cn">靠近、求见证、求回应。</span><span class="en">A reach for closeness, witness, or response.</span></p></article>
      <article class="discovery-card"><h3>breach</h3><p><span class="cn">否认、轻视、抛下、操控。</span><span class="en">Dismissal, denial, abandonment, or coercion.</span></p></article>
      <article class="discovery-card"><h3>repair</h3><p><span class="cn">解释、回收伤害、尝试修复张力。</span><span class="en">Repair work that tries to close tension.</span></p></article>
      <article class="discovery-card"><h3>test / withdrawal / claim</h3><p><span class="cn">试探、撤离、索取位置，都会改写下一轮关系解释。</span><span class="en">Testing, withdrawal, and claims all rewrite the next relational reading.</span></p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="discovery-section">
    <h2 class="section-label"><span class="cn">二元关系场</span><span class="en">Dyadic field</span></h2>
    <div class="metric-strip">
      <div class="metric-cell"><strong>distance</strong><span><span class="cn">当前是在靠近、停留，还是撤离。</span><span class="en">Whether the dyad is closing, holding, or withdrawing.</span></span></div>
      <div class="metric-cell"><strong>safety</strong><span><span class="cn">修复是否还有现实空间。</span><span class="en">Whether repair still feels possible.</span></span></div>
      <div class="metric-cell"><strong>boundary pressure</strong><span><span class="cn">边界是否正被推挤到需要反作用。</span><span class="en">Whether boundary pressure is climbing toward resistance.</span></span></div>
      <div class="metric-cell"><strong>unfinished tension</strong><span><span class="cn">哪些东西没结掉，会在后面几轮继续泄露。</span><span class="en">What remains unresolved and will leak into later turns.</span></span></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="discovery-section">
    <h2 class="section-label"><span class="cn">记忆不是事件表，而是未完成张力</span><span class="en">Memory as unfinished tension</span></h2>
    <div class="split-grid">
      <div class="split-panel">
        <h3><span class="cn">open loops</span><span class="en">open loops</span></h3>
        <p><span class="cn">优先保存未被回应的靠近、未完成的修复、被压下但没消失的冒犯。真实关系最像人的部分，不是记住内容，而是记住没结掉的东西。</span><span class="en">Psyche prioritizes unresolved bids, unfinished repair, and suppressed-but-not-cleared breaches. The human part of memory is often the unresolved tension, not the event log.</span></p>
      </div>
      <div class="split-panel">
        <h3><span class="cn">silent carry</span><span class="en">silent carry</span></h3>
        <p><span class="cn">切回工作时，关系余波不会消失，只是被压进更克制的表达层。任务做完再拉回来，余震还在。</span><span class="en">Switching to work does not erase residue. It pushes it into a quieter layer of behavior so the aftereffect survives task turns.</span></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="discovery-section">
    <h2 class="section-label"><span class="cn">修复为什么不会一句归零</span><span class="en">Why repair does not instantly zero out</span></h2>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="discovery-card">
        <h3><span class="cn">repair hysteresis</span><span class="en">repair hysteresis</span></h3>
        <p><span class="cn">修复可以缓解，但会滞后，不会把此前的 breach 直接冲掉。</span><span class="en">Repair can soften tension with lag. It does not instantly wash out the breach.</span></p>
      </article>
      <article class="discovery-card">
        <h3><span class="cn">repair friction</span><span class="en">repair friction</span></h3>
        <p><span class="cn">重复“我知道了”“对不起”会开始钝化。修复不是越多越有效。</span><span class="en">Repeated “I know” or “sorry” starts to dull out. More repair is not always better repair.</span></p>
      </article>
      <article class="discovery-card">
        <h3><span class="cn">partner-specific meaning</span><span class="en">partner-specific meaning</span></h3>
        <p><span class="cn">同一句“我知道”在高安全关系里可能是 repair，在低安全高压力关系里可能是 withdrawal。</span><span class="en">The same “I know” can register as repair in a safe dyad and withdrawal in a pressured one.</span></p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</DiscoveryPage>
